The paper deals with planar graphs and their visualization, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of grids and the focus on efficient algorithms suggest that the paper may also belong to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of monotone paths and directions in the drawing may also relate to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's emphasis on visualization and its potential applications in various fields suggest that it may also belong to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
